{"title": "New Neighbours as the Plot Demands", "content": "Barbie: My BFF is coming to stay with us for a couple of days!\n\nA Sub-Trope of Geographic Flexibility, when writing a small town setting for long enough, you start introducing new characters everyone apparently knows, but has never mentioned before. In Police Procedural and medical shows, new neighbours are handy for Ripped from the Headlines and Subculture of the Week plots.\n\nCan be a feature of a Quirky Town. If the city was larger, it'd be a City of Adventure. See also 24-Hour Party People, Long-Lost Uncle Aesop, and Remember the New Guy?.\n\nCompare/contrast M\u00f6bius Neighborhood, where the main characters only seem to have one set of next-door neighbours.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NewNeighboursAsThePlotDemands", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/SamAndMaxFreelancePolice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheDukesOfHazzard", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RLStine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Smallville", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Everwood", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Heartbeat", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MurderSheWrote", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/PeakPractice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/RobinHood", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Eureka", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MidsomerMurders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekTheNextGeneration", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/LittleHouseOnThePrairie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/FatherTed", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Charmed1998", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/EnemyAtTheDoor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AnimalCrossing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/WarioWare", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheSims", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheSims2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheSims3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/RealityOnTheNorm", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TheInexplicableAdventuresOfBob", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheSimpsons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Fill